      "text": "Routine home health wound care visit. Findings: erythema and edema of skin surrounding the pressure ulcer, greenish-yellow (purulent) drainage, foul odor, low-grade fever. Patient reports no appetite and increased right hip pain. Nurse suspects wound infection; PCP consulted and recommended evaluation at the emergency department."
